<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monodactylus">Nothrus monodactylus</taxonomicName>
(Berlese, 1910) (non Michael, 1888)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1885" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1885" class="Arachnida" family="Lohmanniidae" genus="Angelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="anauniensis" variety="monodactyla">Angelia anauniensis var. monodactyla Berlese</taxonomicName>
, 1910b, p. 381.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monodactylus">Nothrus monodactylus</taxonomicName>
, Jacot, 1937a, p. 354.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
In the original diagnosis of the &quot; variety &quot; the monodactylous legs and the measurements (0.820 X 0.420 mm, posterior notogastral hairs probably included) are mentioned only. Jacot gave the present combination of names to the species and supposed (without having seen the species) that it is closely related to, or even synonymous with 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="terminalis" subSpecies="carolinae">Nothrus terminalis carolinae Jacot</taxonomicName>
(1937a, p. 354). The name 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1885" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1885" class="Arachnida" family="Lohmanniidae" genus="Angelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="anauniensis" variety="monodactylus">A. anauniensis var. monodactylus</taxonomicName>
points, however, to 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestris">Nothrus silvestris</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="63" pageNumber="64">In the Berlese Collection three types are present (nos. 121/36, 37, 38); they originate from Columbia, Missouri (U.S.A.). The material is damaged; h2 is lacking in all specimens. The length is 0.770-0.785, the breadth 0.400 mm; the length of the notogastral hairs ps1 is only 0.065 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
The species apears indeed to be related to 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestris">Nothrus silvestris</taxonomicName>
, although the bad condition of the specimens does not allow of a definite conclusion. I remark that 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monodactylus">Nothrus monodactylus (Berlese)</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Malaconothridae" genus="Malaconothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monodactylus">Malaconothrus monodactylus (Michael)</taxonomicName>
are secondary homonyms.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
